President Obama spoke with President Recep Tayyip Erdogan of Turkey to express condolences for the recent terrorist attacks in Istanbul and Kayseri. They agreed on the importance of standing united to defeat terrorism and discussed Turkey's efforts to facilitate a ceasefire in Syria and political negotiations. They also noted progress in the fight against ISIL and emphasized the need for continued coordination between the US and Turkey. Additionally, they discussed the issue of Cyprus and expressed hope for a reunification agreement.